what_happens_next: Malcolm Turnbull has pledged to introduce a bill in parliament and has stated he intends for same-sex marriage to be legalised by the end of the year. The bill may be negotiated by MPs seeking laws that would allow businesses to discriminate against same-sex couples. This may delay the passage of the bill.
According to research by the ABC, a vote on a same-sex marriage bill will pass both houses of parliament.
